    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer underflow in LBT DRS request PDU packing\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_lbt_drs_req_pdu_rel13_value` function in the NFAPI P7 packing routines suffered from integer underflow when calculating TLV lengths. This occurred due to incorrect byte ordering in the underlying push/pull functions, which caused the length field to be interpreted as a negative value when cast to unsigned, resulting in extremely large TLV length values.\n\nThe issue manifested during LBT (Listen-Before-Talk) DL configuration request processing, where malformed TLV structures were generated, leading to buffer overflows and potential crashes in the receiving PHY layer.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Corrected byte ordering in push16, pushs16, push32, pushs32, pull16, pulls16, pull32, and pulls32 functions for little-endian platforms\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Fixed return values in simple push/pull functions to return 1 on success instead of byte counts\n\n"
}